&lt;p&gt;CONSULTANT COMMUNITY PAEDIATRICIAN&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking to appoint Community Consultant within the department of Paediatrics to partake in delivering an integrated based Paediatric service with specialist responsibility involving multi agency working with health, education and social care partners. The post is for 10 Programmed Activities (PAs) per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful applicant will work alongside other named professionals for safeguarding and looked after Children’s Services, relevant named nurses, named doctors, GPs and other professionals across Walsall. Whilst this is being advertised as generic community consultant posts, the post holder will be actively encouraged to develop and lead the services for Special Education Needs. Currently this post will also include participation in Child Protection on-Call (9am-5pm).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The full Person Specifications attached to the Job Descriptions list the full requirements, experience and qualifications required for these posts.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameDr Anjan BhaduriJob titleClinical Director - Paediatrics, Consultant PaediatricianEmail addressanjan.bhaduri@walsallhealthcare.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
